{
  "texts": [
    "Query formulation entails transforming the original query into a format suitable for each data source, ensuring that the search is performed effectively.",
    "Search execution involves interfacing with the data sources, performing searches based on the formulated queries, and retrieving the relevant data.",
    "Result ranking is the final step, where the retrieved data is evaluated and ranked based on its relevance and accuracy.",
    "The top-ranked results are then forwarded to the reverse proxy layer, which enriches the original queries and passes them to the Llama model for response generation.Mathematically, the retrieval process can be expressed as follows:Q → f (Q) = Q ′ S (Q ′) = Ω r(x) dx R = arg max x∈Ω S (Q ′)where Q is the original query, f (Q) is the query formulation function transforming Q into Q ′, S (Q ′) represents the search function evaluating the relevance of the query Q ′ over the data source space Ω, and R denotes the top-ranked retrieved data.The integration of the retrieval mechanism with the Llama model is seamless, allowing for dynamic incorporation of external information into the generative process.",
    "By accessing a diverse set of data sources and employing a robust retrieval mechanism, the system ensures that the Llama model generates factually accurate and contextually appropriate responses, addressing the challenges of factual inaccuracy in LLMs."
  ]
}